Watch my face transform! 
Over the last month, I’ve been working with the very knowledgeable beauty injector Julia at the @vivadayspa S Lamar location to subtly enhance my facial structure with @juvederm. 
I knew I’d love some support around the chin and jawline and a pinch in the lips… however, I was so pleasantly surprised by Julia’s recommendations to add support in the upper cheek and behind the masseter muscles at the start of the jaw line which started subtly building the symmetry I’m looking for. 

We used a touch of JUVÉDERM® VOLUMA® XC in the cheeks, JUVÉDERM® VOLBELLA® XC in the lips, and JUVÉDERM® VOLUX® XC in the chin and jawline. 

I’m so grateful for a little glow up with Viva Day Spa, Juvederm, and Julia. I’d say for sure, the 3 V’s from Juvederm is the perfect combo to replenish a youthful appearance. 

*Results vary. Intended for US audiences only. For important safety information, see @juvederm #juvedermcoopprogram

Has anyone heard of a wellness pod before???

Honestly might be my new favorite thing. I basically took a nap for an hour while this thing massaged my body to move my lymph system and healed my cells through red light therapy. You can choose to turn up the heat for some extra sweat relief but my body has but it’s 104 out so I’m good will wait to try out that feature in the winter months 😅 so I just comfortably laid back in the vibration and chilled and let the pod do it’s thing. 

Also, craziest fact is that I found this wellness pod at @organicbronzeatx which is an organic spray tanning salon but what I’ve been noticing is how these smart businesses have traded out UV tanning booths for red light therapy systems because they’re all about improving and preserving the look and health of your skin and body. 

Next I’ll be trying out their organic spray tans. 🤍

If you’re in Austin, check them out!!
(If you need someone jn LA, I’ll connect you to my girl, Flo)

We had a super special cacao ceremony at the @belmondelencanto in Santa Barbara for wellness week. It’s such a beautiful heart opener. 
We were asked to use one word for our intention. Mine was “healing”. 

Cacao is a super food that is known to help blood pressure and inflammation. The nitric oxide actually helps relax your arteries and blood vessels, literally perfect for what I need. Even helps with leg swelling. I should drink this every day. (I’ve been using it as a chocolate alternative for years in smoothies).

Still haven’t shared the depths of physical illness and challenges I’ve been going through for many reasons, part being the little life force I’ve had but I have gotten over the scary hump and the world has a way of guiding you to healing once you can fully surrender. 🧘🏼‍♀️ Santa Barbara has always had magical healing properties for me in general. 

Thank you @kyleecampbell and our friends at @belmondelencanto for this beautiful and very needed wellness week. More to share coming soon in stories. 🙏🏻🫶🏻

Beauty Back Story:

I was the 13 year old in the early 2000’s roaming the isles of CVS attracted to all the new beauty products and buying anti aging creams, clearasil pads, which I did not need and had quite a love for Ponds. 

At 16, in 2003 after an auto immune diagnosis rending me one of the original “gluten free” peeps - I quickly had to become accustom to reading labels that extended beyond food and into beauty products.

Fast forward to my career, social media, and the last few years of a bad bout of unexpected, unwarranted illness, and I’ve been amping up my beauty knowledge to share.

Over the last few years I’ve really done a deep dive into brands that have been able to help bring my glow back. (I was struggling. I didn’t share it all, but it got bad). 

Excited to continue sharing more as I build back my energy and get the business back to into a flow. 🤍✨

Letting go of…

…the trauma I went through (and Minnie too) over the last several years. 

It’s been a wild ride. 

The last few years I didn’t share what I was really dealing with behind the scenes. For multiple reasons, but for some, I was merely just surviving, and fighting to keep any thread of my life and business intact.  Every day I chose life and to push forward even when I wasn’t sure there was a forward to push towards. 

I’m also a private griever and need lots of space to process and I’m happy I’m finally at a point where I am well enough to feel some space from what you see in the pictures. 

The quick physical recap: my body was up against toxicity  for years it accumulated and wore down my immune system. Targeting my respiratory, my lung anti bodies went down to next to nothing to fight off infection (it used up all it could - great timing for when C came around lol) and my airways became so inflamed they were only open 1/4 of the way. 

If anyone knows anything about how your body works at its core, your heart and your lungs are at the center at its life force and they’re very much tied in together. We know your heart pumps blood and lungs bring oxygen to your body. Your heart and lungs work as partners to bring oxygen through blood to all your organs. Lungs are also the main mover (along side muscle action) to move the lymphatic system which is the system that removes toxins. 
If your blood isn’t circulating, your lymphatic system isn’t removing toxicity, your body is going to have a hard time winning against whatever it’s fighting and that’s what was happening to me. 

It got so bad and my body was pushed so far I had the craziest symptoms and ailments. The worst of it was the POTs and chronic migraine symptoms that paired with the swelling and chronic pain and nausea in body. I literally could not stand on my feet without getting swollen legs after 3 hrs and my heart rate in my stress test jumped to 180 in just 2 1/2 mins of walking. (Hard to believe for anyone who has known me all through my career especially those lululemon days of back to back soulcycle classes and Orange theory challenges.) 

(Continues in comments….)
